    "questionType": "programming",
    "sourceUrl": "",
    "content": {
      "text": "No Greater Than X in BST\n\nYou are supposed to output, in decreasing order, all the elements no greater than `X` in a binary search tree `T`.\n\nThe function is supposed to use `Output(X)` to print `X`.\n\n```c\ntypedef struct TreeNode *Tree;\nstruct TreeNode {\n    int Element;\n    Tree  Left;\n    Tree  Right;\n};\n```\n\nFunction signature:\n```c\nvoid Print_NGT( Tree T, int X );\n```",
      "imageUrls": [
        "assets/remote/images.ptausercontent.com/94.jpg",
        "assets/remote/images.ptausercontent.com/95.jpg"
      ]
    },
    "options": [],
    "answer": {
      "text": "",
      "correctOptionIds": [],
      "codeSnippet": "void Print_NGT( Tree T, int X ) {\n    if ( T == NULL ) return;\n    Print_NGT( T->Right, X );\n    if ( T->Element <= X )\n        Output( T->Element );\n    else {\n        Print_NGT( T->Left, X );\n        return;\n    }\n    Print_NGT( T->Left, X );\n}",
      "codeLanguage": "C"
    },
    "difficulty": "hard",
    "tag": [
      "binary search tree",
      "BST",
      "recursion",
      "traversal"
    ]
  },
